#compdef synapse
# ============================================================================
# synapse - LambdaTest Test-at-Scale (TAS) self-hosted runner (Go, Apache-2.0)
#
# Author : LambdaTest team
# Upstream: https://github.com/LambdaTest/test-at-scale
#
# `synapse` is the open-source self-hosted runner for
# LambdaTest's "Test at Scale" platform - a parallelized
# test-orchestration product that takes a repo's test suite,
# computes a per-PR set of affected tests via call-graph
# analysis, then dispatches the affected subset across
# isolated Docker containers in parallel. The synapse binary
# runs on the customer's own infrastructure as a long-lived
# daemon - it polls LambdaTest's cloud control plane for
# work, spawns ephemeral Docker containers per assigned test
# job, streams logs back, and uploads result artifacts.
#
# Architecture: cobra root with two main goroutines -
# `synapse.InitiateConnection` (control-plane WebSocket
# heartbeat + work assignment) and `proxyserver.ListenAndServe`
# (local HTTP proxy that test runs use for outbound
# request capture). Each test job spawns via the docker
# runner package; per-test artifact upload + log streaming
# goes back to the cloud over the same control-plane
# connection. A cron scheduler manages periodic tasks like
# garbage-collecting stale containers + config refresh.
#
# Usage:
#   synapse [flags]
#
# Flags (cobra):
#   -c, --config <file>     - config file path
#       --verbose           - log every proxy request to stdout
#   -h, --help              - print help
#       --version           - print version
#
# Environment:
#   Standard .env file loading via joho/godotenv -
#   credentials + per-repo secrets are layered from .env
#   + the loaded config + the cloud control plane.
#
# The cenkalti/backoff lane is built on `github.com/cenkalti/
# backoff/v4 v4.1.3` (declared as a direct dep at upstream
# go.mod HEAD), the canonical Go exponential-backoff retry
# library by Cenk Altı (github.com/cenkalti/backoff, 2600+
# stars). cenkalti/backoff is the *original* implementation
# of the Google-SRE-book exponential-backoff-with-jitter
# pattern in Go - released in 2014 and adopted as the
# de-facto standard across the Go ecosystem. The /v4 module
# adds context-aware `BackOffWithContext` for cancellation,
# the `Notify` callback for observability, and
# `Permanent(err)` to bail out early on non-retryable
# errors. synapse uses it for: cloud-control-plane reconnect
# (WebSocket disconnects retry with exponential backoff up
# to a max-elapsed-time), Docker daemon API calls (transient
# 503 / dial timeouts retry inside the per-job runner), and
# artifact-upload S3 calls (rate-limit + transient-failure
# retry).
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 233 :: Exponential-backoff retry policies (idempotent retry gates)
# Round 1398 :: Go slot 2 of 4 :: continues Axis 233
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : ihrwein/backoff              [R1397 _oramacore]
#   Go      : cenkalti/backoff             [R1398 THIS FILE]
#   TS/Node : vercel/async-retry           [R1399 closing]
#
# cenkalti/backoff is the *source* of this axis - the
# original 2014 Go implementation that the Rust slot
# (ihrwein/backoff) is a line-by-line port of, and that
# every other Go retry library traces design-influence to.
# This is a rare pattern across the 233 axes covered so far:
# usually the canonical library in each lane is the
# *independent* implementation by the native-language
# community of a spec or paper. Axis 233 instead has a
# canonical lane (Go) with a direct downstream port lane
# (Rust) and an API-similar-but-independent lane (Node).
# The cross-language consistency is therefore strongest
# between the Rust + Go slots and looser between Go + Node.
#
# All three lanes implement the same algorithmic pattern
# (initial interval + multiplier + max interval +
# max-elapsed-time + ±50% jitter) with subtly different
# default parameters (`ExponentialBackoff` defaults: 500ms
# / 1.5x / 60s / 15min; vercel/async-retry defaults: 1000ms
# / 2x / unbounded / 10 retries) - the choice of defaults
# reflects each lane's typical workload (HTTP retry for
# Node, RPC retry for Go).
# ============================================================================

_synapse() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '(-c --config)'{-c,--config}'[config file path]:file:_files' \
        '--verbose[log every proxy request to stdout]' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]' \
        '(- *)--version[print version]'
}

_synapse "$@"
